Cape Town residents have called for the implementation of such laws in the Mother City to prevent unaffordable rates. CAPE TOWN Rent control laws aim to keep property rentals at an affordable rate. Cape Town residents have called for the implementation of such laws in the Mother City to prevent unaffordable rates which force the working class on the outskirts of the city. Koketso Sachane speaks to Professor Francois Viruly at the University of Cape Town s Property Development Studies.